Splunk Enterprise Installation (Main Windows Machine)
Step 1: Download Splunk Enterprise

Visit the official Splunk Enterprise download page:

https://www.splunk.com/en_us/download/splunk-enterprise.html

Download the Windows 64-bit installer.

note : must and should need to create a account 

Step 2: Install Splunk Enterprise
Open the downloaded installer.
Accept the license agreement.
Select "Local System" when prompted.
Create an administrator username and password.
Click Install.
Wait for the installation to complete.
Step 3: Access Splunk

Open a web browser and navigate to:

http://localhost:8000

Log in using the administrator credentials created during installation.

Outcome

Splunk Enterprise is successfully installed and ready to be configured as the central SIEM server for collecting, monitoring, and analyzing security logs from the SOC lab environment.
